{"word":"ναυπηγέω","slug":"ναυπηγέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ναυπηγέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ναυπηγός'><el>ναυπηγός</el></a>\n<p/><i>to build ships</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>: —<a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <el>ναῦς ναυπηγέεσθαι</el> <i>to build oneself</i> ships, <i>get them built</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, of ships, <i>to be built</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/>"}]}